getFacetDisplayValue

public java.lang.String getFacetDisplayValue()
Get the display value of the Facet. This is not the selected facet item, but the facet itself. For Example Facet "cities" with Display Name "Cities" may have many facet items in the LOV. This is typically shown in the Tile label.

Returns:
Facet Display Value "Cities".

setAllFacetItemsAvailable

public void setAllFacetItemsAvailable(boolean allFacetItemsAvailable)
Set whether all facet values are available (as opposed to there are none for the user to see). This can occur when Saved/Recent searches with deep facet paths are run - the intermediate Facets will not have facet Items populated and will need to be independently queried for.

Parameters:
allFacetItemsAvailable - true if available, false if a phantom query is required to obtain them.

isAllFacetItemsAvailable

public boolean isAllFacetItemsAvailable()
Get whether all facet values are available (as opposed to there are none for the user to see). This can occur when Saved/Recent searches with deep facet paths are run - the intermediate Facets will not have facet Items populated and will need to be independently queried for.

Returns:
true if available, false if a phantom query is required to obtain them.
